The paper discusses the detection of vulnerabilities in smart contracts, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed approach involves the use of machine learning, specifically long-short term memory (LSTM), which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and programming languages (cs.PL).
